# Feature Design-First Policy

**Do not implement a new feature until a design document exists in `features/<feature-name>.md`.**

## Before writing any code for a new feature

1. Create `features/<feature-name>.md` using the template at `features/FEATURE_TEMPLATE.md`
2. The document must cover: purpose, user journey, data model changes, component breakdown, IPC changes (if any), and open questions
3. Only begin implementation after the design is reviewed and accepted

## Reusability is a primary concern

- Before creating a new component, check if an existing base component can be extended or composed
- Extract any logic used in more than one place into a composable (`src/composables/`) or service
- Prefer composition over duplication — a second use of the same pattern is the signal to abstract it
- New Pinia stores should be scoped to a feature domain; never create a catch-all store

## Checklist when adding a feature

- [ ] `features/<feature-name>.md` exists and is complete
- [ ] No new component duplicates an existing one
- [ ] Reusable logic is in a composable or service, not inline in a view
- [ ] New components are dumb and have Storybook stories
